  brain_region: 'Default Mode Network',
  brain_region_hi: 'डिफ़ॉल्ट मोड नेटवर्क',
    core_science: 'The Incubation Period is a critical stage in the creative process where the mind is distracted from the target problem, allowing the brain to process it subconsciously. When you focus intensely on a problem, your prefrontal cortex restricts your thinking to familiar pathways. When you step away and engage in a low-demand task, the Default Mode Network activates, allowing the brain to search its database and make unusual, distant connections. This subconscious processing is why creative breakthroughs often happen when you are showering, walking, or resting. Research shows that incubation requires a complete shift in attention; simply sitting at your desk trying to force a solution will not work. By letting go of the problem, you give your brain the freedom to reorganize information and discover the solution.',
    in_your_life: 'When stuck on a difficult project, our habit is to stare at the screen and try to force a breakthrough, which leads to frustration. To unlock your creativity, you must trust your subconscious mind. Intentionally step away from your work and engage in a relaxing activity, allowing your brain to process the problem in the background. This is essential for cognitive growth.',
