  brain_region: 'Mesolimbic Pathway',
  brain_region_hi: 'मेसोलिम्बिक मार्ग',
    core_science: 'Dopamine plays a critical role in the creative process by driving exploration and curiosity. The mesolimbic dopamine pathway is activated when you explore new environments, learn new skills, or seek out unusual information. This dopamine release increases cognitive flexibility, allowing the prefrontal cortex to associate distant ideas and see new patterns. Individuals with highly active dopamine systems often show high levels of open-mindedness and creative achievement. However, this exploration drive must be balanced: too much dopamine can lead to constant distraction, while too little leads to rigid, repetitive thinking. By actively seeking out novel experiences and learning diverse subjects, you can stimulate this dopaminergic drive, providing your brain with the chemical energy and diverse inputs required to generate unique, creative insights.',
    in_your_life: 'When we fall into rigid routines, our brain\'s dopamine pathways slow down, leading to uninspired, repetitive thinking. To spark your creativity, you must introduce novelty into your life. Exploring new subjects, visiting new places, or learning a new skill can stimulate your dopamine pathways, providing fresh energy for your creative projects. This simple shift in perspective can transform how you approach daily tasks.',
