    core_science: 'In our hyper-connected world, we rarely experience boredom. The moment we feel a pause, we check our phones, seeking instant stimulation. However, neuroscience shows that boredom is a critical trigger for creativity. When external stimulation drops, the brain\'s Default Mode Network activates, initiating a process of internal search and daydreaming. This restless mental state encourages the brain to explore its memory archives and connect distant concepts, leading to creative insights and problem-solving. By constantly avoiding boredom with digital distractions, we suppress this default processing, denying our brains the quiet time needed to generate original ideas. Embracing periods of boredom is not a waste of time; it is a biological requirement for creative rejuvenation, deeper self-reflection, and neural healing. This mechanism promotes brain health.',
    in_your_life: 'We view boredom as something to avoid, constantly filling every quiet moment with screen time. This habit leaves our minds feeling overstimulated and uninspired. To spark your creativity, you must allow yourself to be bored. Letting your mind wander during quiet moments can give your brain the space to generate its most original ideas. This simple shift in perspective can transform how you approach daily tasks.',
